            <div type="general">
               <p xml:space="preserve">Amdoun is a town located in the northwest Tunisian Beja Governorate, 13 km to the northwest of the town of Beja.</p>
               <p xml:space="preserve">The Amdoun region is a rural and agriculturally dominated area, characterized by green landscapes. </p>
               <p xml:space="preserve">As for folk religion, the local saints of Amdoun are Sidi Medyen (Sīdi Madyin), Sidi Dakhli (Sīdi Daxli), Sidi Mansour (Sīdi Manṣūṛ) and Sidi Salah (Sīdi Ṣālaḥ), the first of them being the eponym of Amdoun’s alternative name Zahret Medyen.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="researchHistory">
               <p xml:space="preserve">To the best of our knowledge hitherto no research has been done on the dialect of Amdoun, however this dialect is linguistically investigated within the TUNOCENT project.</p>
            </div>
